A cold front is expected to pass over the southern parts of the country on Tuesday night into Wednesday, bringing cooler temperatures and rain along the coast. Temperatures along the coast are expected to be cool to cold, as provided by the South African Weather Service. It will be hot along the northern border and adjacent interior. The weather in your region Gauteng will be fine and warm. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high. Morning fog is expected along the escarpment of Mpumalanga. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool but warm in the Lowveld. Limpopo will be fine and warm but hot in the Lowveld and Limpopo Valley. It will be fine and warm in the North West. The Free State will be partly cloudy and misty in the extreme east at first. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool but warm in the extreme north-east. It will become cloudy in the extreme east during the evening. Morning fog is expected over the southern interior of the Northern Cape where it will be cold. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool becoming fine in the afternoon. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh. It will be cloudy in the north-eastern parts of the Western Cape, with frost in places. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool to cold. Isolated showers and rain are expected in the morning. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate. The Eastern Cape is expected to be cloudy in the north and the east at first. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool to cold with light rain in places. The wind along the coast will be varied. It will be cloudy and cool in KwaZulu-Natal. Scattered showers and rain are expected in the south-east. Otherwise, isolated showers are expected, except in the west. The wind along the coast will be moderate. The expected UVB sunburn index will be low.  Compiled by Naseema Barday Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days